name: MoMgcfIPRouting
desc: This table defines the static IP Routings which will be used on Os level.

mgcfIPRoutingId.name: mgcfIPRoutingId
mgcfIPRoutingId.desc: The MoClass key of the mgcfIPRouting

mgcfRoutingDestination.name: mgcfRoutingDestination
mgcfRoutingDestination.desc: The destination host/net address for this static IP route

mgcfRoutingNetworkMask.name: mgcfRoutingNetworkMask
mgcfRoutingNetworkMask.desc: This parameter defines the network mask for the routing destination IP address

mgcfRoutingNextHop.name: mgcfRoutingNextHop
mgcfRoutingNextHop.desc: The next hop IP address (gateway address) for this static IP route.

mgcfRoutingInterface.name: mgcfRoutingInterface
mgcfRoutingInterface.desc:
Force the route to be associated with the specified device.
MGC uses interface bond0 and it is not changeable. So bond0 will not present into the interface string. Only need to specify VLAN ID here.
For example, if Device Interface parameter value is 311, then the interface in OS will be bond0.311
